WEBVTT

00:10.928 --> 00:13.347
Thank you for your call, Lorraine.

00:13.514 --> 00:17.809
And before the commercial break,
Roz has an important message. Roz?

00:21.605 --> 00:23.941
What? Can't come to the mic?

00:25.817 --> 00:28.570
Well, what she wanted to say was...

00:30.364 --> 00:33.367
Tomorrow, on Amber Edwards'
"Bookchat",

00:33.534 --> 00:37.788
sociologist Lamont Myman
discusses his book,

00:37.955 --> 00:42.543
"Violence in the Workplace -
Why Co-Workers Kill".

00:44.169 --> 00:47.714
Something which becomes
more and more relevant.

00:47.881 --> 00:49.925
We'll be right back.

00:51.009 --> 00:53.804
Open up, you piece of tin!

00:54.638 --> 00:57.057
- Roz!
- What are you doing here?

00:57.224 --> 01:02.437
And you? Shouldn't you wait
till after the show before exiting?

01:03.230 --> 01:07.234
- I have a little urge. Damn it!
- What is the matter?

01:07.609 --> 01:10.571
I have got to have chocolate!

01:13.782 --> 01:15.993
It's kind of a celebration.

01:16.159 --> 01:19.955
At 11:07 am, I finished
one of those magazine diets.

01:20.122 --> 01:23.208
"Seven days
to a healthier, calmer you."

01:24.585 --> 01:28.547
Come on, Roz!
I'm doing this for your own good.

01:28.714 --> 01:31.133
Wait!
Something came out!

01:33.010 --> 01:35.846
Damn! Chocolate-covered raisins.

01:36.013 --> 01:39.683
I'd like to meet the idiot
who came up with these.

01:39.850 --> 01:43.604
Take a grape, let it shrivel
into a disgusting little wart

01:43.770 --> 01:47.024
and cover it
with perfectly good chocolate.

01:47.191 --> 01:50.861
What the hell!
I'll suck the chocolate off.

01:52.696 --> 01:56.033
Be sure to save what's left
to make some wine!

